        <value>To be added.</value>
        <remarks>
          <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
          <para>Validation groups allow you to assign validation controls on a page to a specific category. Each validation group can be validated independently of other validation groups on the page. Use the <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ValidationSummary.ValidationGroup" /> property to specify the name of the validation group for which the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ValidationSummary" /> control will summarize error messages.</para>
          <para>When you specify a value for the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.ValidationSummary" /> property, only error messages from the validation controls that are part of the specified group are summarized. If you do not set a value for this property, all error messages from validation controls on the page that are not assigned to a validation group are summarized.</para>
          <para>This property cannot be set by themes or style sheet themes. For more information, see <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.ThemeableAttribute" /> and <format type="text/html"><a href="5df3ebbd-d46c-4502-9406-02f9df4ef2c3">ASP.NET Themes Overview</a></format>.</para>
        </remarks>
